Package: acr
Title: Adversarial Causal Regularization Without Predefined Environments
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Francisco", "Richter", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "richtf@usi.ch"),
    person(given = c("Ernst", "C."), family = "Wit", role = "aut",
           email = "ernst.jan.camiel.wit@usi.ch"))
Description: Implements adversarial causal regularization (ACR) for learning
    predictors that are robust to distribution shift, without requiring
    predefined environment labels. Supports linear regression, generalized
    linear models (Poisson, binomial), and generalized additive models (via
    mgcv). The two-phase algorithm learns soft environment weights
    adversarially (Phase 1) and selects regularization strength via
    cross-validation (Phase 2).
